ACT:
 Right of opportunity for admission to medical colleges- Rules for Admission into the Medical, Dentistry and Ayurvedic Colleges in Madhya Pradesh prescribing selection purely on merit from amongst those who have qualified in the written examination-Reservation as seats for scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes to the extent of 15% for each category subject to a provision in Rule 9 to the effect that unfilled vacancies should go to candidates available on the combined Merit List-State Government by an executive order dated 9th September, 1980 completely relaxing the conditions relating to the minimum qualification marks for selection to medical colleges in favour of Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes-Whether the executive order offends Articles 14 and 15 of the Constitution and ordinance 54 of the University of Jabalpur, Regulation 2 of the Medical Council of India read with section 19 of the Indian Medical Council Act, 1956.
 
